File: 27 people accused of fraudulently selling South African passports appeared briefly in the Krugersdorp Magistrate's Cour. (eNCA\Screenshot) JOHANNESBURG - The alleged passports syndicate case has been postponed to Friday. READ: Illegal Migration | Fake passport kingpin caught red-handed This follows a sting operation at a Home Affairs office in March, in which 27 people were arrested for allegedly being part of a fake passport syndicate. The accused appeared at the Krugersdorp Magistrate's Court for their bail application on Tuesday. Their case has been adjourned until Friday, 8 April.